## 🧠 Sample Question 1: Energy and Exercises

### Problem Statement
If performing all the exercises does not make you feel tired, return `-1`.

### Parameters
- `E`: INTEGER  
  The first line contains an integer `E`, denoting the Energy.  
  Constraints: `1 ≤ E ≤ 10^5`

- `N`: INTEGER  
  The next line contains an integer `N`, denoting the number of exercises.  
  Constraints: `1 ≤ N ≤ 10^5`

- `A`: INTEGER ARRAY  
  Each line `i` of the `N` subsequent lines (where `0 ≤ i < N`) contains an integer describing the amount of energy drained by the `i`th exercise.  
  Constraints: `A[i] :: 1 ≤ A[i] ≤ 10^5`

---

### 🧪 Case #1

#### Input
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
solution:
#include <iostream>
#include <algorithm>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

int main(){
    int K,N;
    cin>>K;
    cin>>N;

    vector<int> v(N);

    for(int i=0;i<N;i++){
        cin>>v[i];
    }

    sort(v.begin(),v.end(),greater<int>());

    int result=0;
    int i=0;

    while(K>0 && i<N){

        int count=0;

        while(count<2 && K>0){
            K = K - v[i];
            result++;
            count++;
        }

        i++;
    }

    if(K>0)
        cout<<-1;
    else
        cout<<result;
}
